EXISTING STRUCTURES

### Power Generation System at x=-4.5, y=12.5

### Automation Science Pack Production Line at x=8.5, y=13.5
Consists of:
- Assembling machine at x=8.5, y=13.5
- Iron gear input:
  - Storage chest at x=7.5, y=10.5
  - Inserter at x=8.5, y=10.5

  - Output chest at x=11.5, y=13.5
- Transport belt system connecting components

ERROR TIPS

### Entity Placement Collision Errors
- Check for existing entities (belts, chests, poles) before placing new entities
- Use appropriate spacing when placing entities next to each other
- Consider the direction of placement to avoid collisions with existing structures

### Resource Management Issues
- Ensure fuel (coal) is available for burner entities
- Stock required materials before attempting to insert into chests
- Verify ingredient availability before setting up production chains

### Production Line Setup
- Plan the layout carefully to avoid overlapping entity placements
- Consider the space requirements for inserters and chests around assembling machines
- Ensure proper connections between different components of production lines

### Power System Issues
- Keep boilers fueled to maintain consistent power supply
- Monitor power consumption and generation capacity
